to quantify the above questions, 


Head of Sales Op and Head of Growth:
- Sales efficiency;
- Areas to grow

Define the stages:
- awareness (ad spend efficiency)
- consideration (conversions)

To see how well your marketing is doing, you need to check a few things:

Sales: Are you making money from your marketing?

Getting Leads: Is your marketing getting people interested?

Keeping Customers: Are customers sticking around?

Nurturing Leads: Are you taking care of potential customers?

Brand Awareness: Is your brand getting known?

Engagement: Are people engaging with your marketing?

To see if your marketing is profitable, use this formula: (Money you make - Money spent on marketing) / Money spent on marketing.

This shows if you're making more money than you're spending. Connecting marketing to revenue is key to understanding its impact on your bottom line in our data-driven marketing world.


